      • findReachableObject

        public net.runelite.api.GameObject findReachableObject​(java.lang.String objectName,
                                                       boolean exact,
                                                       int distance,
                                                       net.runelite.api.coords.WorldPoint anchorPoint)
        Finds a reachable game object by name within a specified distance from an anchor point.
        Parameters:
        objectName - The name of the game object to find.
        exact - Whether to match the name exactly or partially.
        distance - The maximum distance from the anchor point to search for the game object.
        anchorPoint - The point from which to measure the distance.
        Returns:
        The nearest reachable game object that matches the criteria, or null if none is found.

      • findReachableObject

        public net.runelite.api.GameObject findReachableObject​(java.lang.String objectName,
                                                       boolean exact,
                                                       int distance,
                                                       net.runelite.api.coords.WorldPoint anchorPoint,
                                                       boolean checkAction,
                                                       java.lang.String action)
        Finds a reachable game object by name within a specified distance from an anchor point, optionally checking for a specific action.
        Parameters:
        objectName - The name of the game object to find.
        exact - Whether to match the name exactly or partially.
        distance - The maximum distance from the anchor point to search for the game object.
        anchorPoint - The point from which to measure the distance.
        checkAction - Whether to check for a specific action on the game object.
        action - The action to check for if checkAction is true.
        Returns:
        The nearest reachable game object that matches the criteria, or null if none is found.

      • nameMatches

        public <T extends net.runelite.api.TileObject> java.util.function.Predicate<T> nameMatches​(java.lang.String objectName,
                                                                                           boolean exact)
        Creates a predicate that matches TileObjects whose name matches the given name. Optionally, it can require an exact match or allow partial (contains) match.
        Type Parameters:
        T - A type that extends TileObject.
        Parameters:
        objectName - The name of the object to match.
        exact - If true, the object name must exactly match (case-insensitive). If false, the name must only contain the given string (case-insensitive).
        Returns:
        A predicate that returns true if the object's name matches the given name.
